# DiagramMaker AI — System Architecture Deep Dive

---

## 1. High-Level System Architecture

This is the bird's-eye view of the entire system. Three independent processes collaborate over HTTP:

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph USER["👤 User Browser"]
        UI["Vite Frontend<br/>:5173"]
    end

    subgraph BACKEND["⚙️ FastAPI Backend :8001"]
        API["/api Router"]
        CHAT_SVC["ChatService"]
        DESIGN_SVC["DesignService"]
        REPO["DesignRepository"]
    end

    subgraph EXTERNAL["☁️ External Services"]
        GEMINI["Google Gemini 2.5 Flash"]
    end

    subgraph STORAGE["💾 Persistence"]
        JSON_FILE["data/project_design.json"]
    end

    UI -- "POST /api/chat" --> API
    UI -- "GET /api/design/state" --> API
    UI -- "POST /api/design/operations" --> API
    UI -- "GET /api/health" --> API

    API --> CHAT_SVC
    API --> DESIGN_SVC
    CHAT_SVC -- "Gemini SDK" --> GEMINI
    DESIGN_SVC --> REPO
    REPO -- "Read/Write JSON" --> JSON_FILE

    style USER fill:#1a1a2e,stroke:#c4a882,color:#e8e4df
    style BACKEND fill:#16213e,stroke:#c4a882,color:#e8e4df
    style EXTERNAL fill:#0f3460,stroke:#c4a882,color:#e8e4df
    style STORAGE fill:#1a1a2e,stroke:#c4a882,color:#e8e4df
```

### How It Works

The system is a **two-service architecture** (frontend + backend) with one external dependency (Gemini API):

| Component | Technology | Port | Responsibility |
|-----------|-----------|------|----------------|
| **Frontend** | Vite + Vanilla JS + Cytoscape.js | `5173` | Renders the 3-panel UI (chat, canvas, settings), manages user interactions, sends HTTP requests to backend |
| **Backend** | FastAPI + Pydantic + Uvicorn | `8001` | Serves 4 API endpoints, validates all design mutations, persists state, proxies AI chat to Gemini |
| **Gemini API** | Google `gemini-2.5-flash` | Cloud | Provides system-design-focused AI responses via the `google-generativeai` SDK |
| **Design State** | JSON file on disk | N/A | Single file (`data/project_design.json`) acting as the canonical source of truth for the diagram |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Core principle**: The **backend owns the design state**. The frontend and AI never directly mutate the design document. They send validated operations to the backend, which applies them against a canonical document.

---

## 2. Backend Layered Architecture

The backend follows a **clean-architecture / layered** pattern with 5 distinct layers:

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph DELIVERY["Delivery Layer (API Routes)"]
        R_HEALTH["/api/health<br/>health.py"]
        R_CHAT["/api/chat<br/>chat.py"]
        R_DESIGN_GET["/api/design/state<br/>design.py"]
        R_DESIGN_POST["/api/design/operations<br/>design.py"]
    end

    subgraph APPLICATION["Application Layer (Services)"]
        SVC_CHAT["ChatService<br/>chat_service.py"]
        SVC_DESIGN["DesignService<br/>design_service.py"]
    end

    subgraph DOMAIN["Domain Layer (Models)"]
        M_CHAT["ChatRequest / ChatResponse<br/>ChatMessage"]
        M_DESIGN["DiagramDocument / DiagramNode<br/>DiagramEdge / DiagramOperation<br/>ProjectContext"]
    end

    subgraph PERSISTENCE["Persistence Layer (Repositories)"]
        REPO_DESIGN["DesignRepository<br/>design_repository.py"]
    end

    subgraph INFRA["Infrastructure Layer (Core)"]
        CONFIG["Settings / Config<br/>config.py"]
        MAIN["FastAPI App<br/>main.py"]
    end

    R_CHAT --> SVC_CHAT
    R_DESIGN_GET --> SVC_DESIGN
    R_DESIGN_POST --> SVC_DESIGN

    SVC_CHAT --> M_CHAT
    SVC_DESIGN --> M_DESIGN

    SVC_DESIGN --> REPO_DESIGN
    REPO_DESIGN --> M_DESIGN

    SVC_CHAT --> CONFIG
    MAIN --> CONFIG

    style DELIVERY fill:#1e3a5f,stroke:#c4a882,color:#e8e4df
    style APPLICATION fill:#1a3050,stroke:#c4a882,color:#e8e4df
    style DOMAIN fill:#162540,stroke:#c4a882,color:#e8e4df
    style PERSISTENCE fill:#121e30,stroke:#c4a882,color:#e8e4df
    style INFRA fill:#0e1820,stroke:#c4a882,color:#e8e4df
```

### Layer-by-Layer Breakdown

#### Layer 1: Infrastructure — [main.py](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/backend/app/main.py) + [config.py](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/backend/app/core/config.py)

- Creates the `FastAPI` app instance with project metadata
- Configures **CORS middleware** so the Vite dev server at `:5173` can call the API at `:8001`
- Loads environment variables via `dotenv` (specifically `GEMINI_API_KEY`)
- Mounts the unified `api_router` under the `/api` prefix

#### Layer 2: Delivery — [router.py](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/backend/app/api/router.py) + Routes

The router aggregates 3 route modules into one `APIRouter`:

| Route | Method | Handler | Purpose |
|-------|--------|---------|---------|
| `/api/health` | GET | [health.py](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/backend/app/api/routes/health.py) | Returns service status + whether Gemini key is configured |
| `/api/chat` | POST | [chat.py](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/backend/app/api/routes/chat.py) | Accepts user message + history, returns AI response |
| `/api/design/state` | GET | [design.py](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/backend/app/api/routes/design.py) | Returns the full design document (nodes, edges, project context) |
| `/api/design/operations` | POST | [design.py](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/backend/app/api/routes/design.py) | Applies a batch of validated operations to the design document |

#### Layer 3: Application — [chat_service.py](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/backend/app/services/chat_service.py) + [design_service.py](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/backend/app/services/design_service.py)

**ChatService**: Configures `gemini-2.5-flash` with a system design prompt, builds chat history from the frontend's conversation log, and returns the model's response. Gracefully degrades with an error message if the API key is missing.

**DesignService**: The heart of the system. It processes a list of `DiagramOperation` objects sequentially, applying each against the in-memory document. It validates constraints (unique IDs, existing nodes for edges), increments the version counter, and persists via the repository.

#### Layer 4: Domain — [chat/models.py](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/backend/app/domain/chat/models.py) + [design/models.py](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/backend/app/domain/design/models.py)

All data contracts are Pydantic `BaseModel` classes with strict validation. The `DiagramOperation` model uses a `@model_validator` to ensure each operation type carries its required payload.

#### Layer 5: Persistence — [design_repository.py](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/backend/app/repositories/design_repository.py)

Reads/writes the design document as JSON to `data/project_design.json`. Creates a default starter document if the file doesn't exist.

