## 3. Domain Model Hierarchy

```mermaid
classDiagram
    class DiagramDocument {
        +ProjectContext project
        +List~DiagramNode~ nodes
        +List~DiagramEdge~ edges
        +int version
        +str updated_at
    }

    class ProjectContext {
        +str name
        +str summary
        +str design_type
        +List~str~ assumptions
        +List~str~ requirements
    }

    class DiagramNode {
        +str id
        +DiagramNodeData data
        +DiagramNodePosition position
    }

    class DiagramNodeData {
        +str label
        +str kind
        +Dict metadata
    }

    class DiagramNodePosition {
        +float x
        +float y
    }

    class DiagramEdge {
        +str id
        +str source
        +str target
        +DiagramEdgeData data
    }

    class DiagramEdgeData {
        +str|None label
        +Dict metadata
    }

    class DiagramOperation {
        +str type
        +DiagramNode|None node
        +DiagramEdge|None edge
        +str|None node_id
        +str|None edge_id
        +Dict updates
        +ProjectContext|None project
        +validate_payload()
    }

    class ApplyOperationsRequest {
        +List~DiagramOperation~ operations
    }

    class ApplyOperationsResponse {
        +DiagramDocument document
        +int applied_operations
    }

    DiagramDocument *-- ProjectContext
    DiagramDocument *-- DiagramNode
    DiagramDocument *-- DiagramEdge
    DiagramNode *-- DiagramNodeData
    DiagramNode *-- DiagramNodePosition
    DiagramEdge *-- DiagramEdgeData
    ApplyOperationsRequest *-- DiagramOperation
    ApplyOperationsResponse *-- DiagramDocument
```

### The 7 Operation Types

| Operation | Required Fields | What It Does |
|-----------|----------------|--------------|
| `add_node` | `node` (full DiagramNode) | Validates ID uniqueness, appends node to document |
| `update_node` | `node_id` + `updates` dict | Finds node by ID, patches label/kind/position/metadata |
| `delete_node` | `node_id` | Removes node AND all connected edges (cascade delete) |
| `add_edge` | `edge` (full DiagramEdge) | Validates edge ID uniqueness + both source/target nodes exist |
| `delete_edge` | `edge_id` | Removes edge by ID |
| `clear_diagram` | (none) | Empties both `nodes[]` and `edges[]` |
| `set_project_context` | `project` | Replaces the entire project context |

> [!NOTE]
> Operations are applied **sequentially** in a single transaction. The version counter increments once per batch, not per operation. This means a single `POST /api/design/operations` with 5 operations produces one version bump.

