### Frontend Module Details

#### [main.js](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/frontend/src/app/main.js) — Bootstrap
Waits for `DOMContentLoaded`, then initializes the 3 feature modules in order: Chat → Canvas → Settings. Also imports the global CSS.

#### [canvas.js](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/frontend/src/features/canvas/canvas.js) — The Core Feature (~430 lines)
- **On init**: Calls `GET /api/design/state` to load the backend document, falls back to a hardcoded `FALLBACK_DOCUMENT` on error
- **Renders** nodes and edges into a Cytoscape.js graph with a preset layout
- **Every mutation** (add node, delete node, add edge, update label, etc.) first calls `POST /api/design/operations`, then updates the local Cytoscape graph
- **Supports**: right-click context menus, double-tap label editing, keyboard shortcuts (Delete, Ctrl+A), connect mode for drawing edges, zoom controls

#### [chat.js](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/frontend/src/features/chat/chat.js) — AI Chat Panel
- Maintains an in-memory `conversationHistory[]` array
- On send: pushes user message, calls `POST /api/chat` with full history, renders AI response with markdown formatting
- Checks backend health on startup to set connection status indicator

#### [settings.js](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/frontend/src/features/settings/settings.js) — Configuration Panel
- **Canvas toggles**: Grid overlay (CSS background-image), snap-to-grid (Cytoscape `free` event handler), minimap (placeholder)
- **Node styling**: Live color picker and shape selector applied to Cytoscape styles
- **Actions**: Auto-layout (grid algorithm), Export JSON, Clear Canvas (calls backend's `clear_diagram` operation)
- **Accordion**: Collapsible sections via `section-header` / `section-body` toggling

#### [apiClient.js](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/frontend/src/shared/api/apiClient.js) — HTTP Client
4 exported functions wrapping `fetch()`:

```
checkBackendHealth()         → GET  /api/health
sendChatMessage(msg, hist)   → POST /api/chat
fetchDesignState()           → GET  /api/design/state
applyDesignOperations(ops)   → POST /api/design/operations
```

All responses are parsed through a shared `parseJsonResponse()` that extracts error details from FastAPI's `HTTPException` format.

#### [formatters.js](file:///d:/Worked/proj/B__Professonal__B/AI-based-Dia-maker/main_file/frontend/src/shared/utils/formatters.js) — Shared Utilities
- `escapeHtml()` — XSS-safe text rendering
- `formatMarkdown()` — Lightweight markdown→HTML (code blocks, bold, italic, lists)
- `getTimestamp()` — HH:MM for chat messages
- `showToast()` — Ephemeral notification system

